==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mulch
<hw>Mulch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <ets>mull</ets>
dirt, also Prov. G. <ets>mulsch</ets>, <ets>molsch</ets>, rotten, soft,
mellow, as fruit.]</ety> <def>Half-rotten straw, or any similar light,
porous, organic substance strewn on the ground, as over the roots of
plants, to protect from heat, drought, etc., and to hinder weed growth
and preserve moisture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mulch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mulch
<hw>Mulch</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Mulched</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Mulching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To cover or dress with
mulch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mulct</ent>⟦br⟧
